Following the instructions outlined in section II of the [http://docs.google.com/View?docid=dzprnmw_10gk2mcpfb use Protege with OBI] document. Set the obi-quick-id.owl file as the active ontology file.

Once selected as active all new classes added to the ontology via Protege will be added to the obi-quick-id.owl file.

== I have a term I would like to add to OBI, where do I start? ==

OBI uses the [http://www.ifomis.org/bfo Basic Formal Ontology] (BFO) as an upper ontology to provide a framework in support of domain ontologies developed for scientific research. When submitting a term to OBI consideration should be given as to which node of BFO the term should be inferred under. For example, is the term a process, a material entity or information that describes an entity?

